==Production==
After the Arjun-directed ''[[Ezhumalai]]'', the Arjun-Simran pair come together in yet another film titled <U+2018>Ottran<U+2019>. Directing the film is first-timer Ilankannan, who had apprenticed with director Shanker. Arjun plays a secret agent in the film, which gives him scope for enough of action scenes. Shooting commenced in Chennai in a forty-day schedule.<ref>http://web.archive.org/web/20030210121457/http://www.chennaionline.com/location/index.asp</ref>

==Soundtrack==

These 6 songs in ''Ottran'' are composed by [[Pravin Mani]].<ref>http://www.raaga.com/channels/tamil/moviedetail.asp?mid=T0000546</ref>

*"Yeh Thiththippey" - [[Karthik (singer)|Karthik]], [[Suchitra]]
*"Oru Paarvai"  - [[Srinivas (singer)|Srinivas]], [[Sujatha Mohan|Sujatha]]
*"Chinna Veeda"  -  [[Manikka Vinayagam]], [[Srilekha Parthasarathy]]
*"Kitchu Kitchu"  -  [[Shankar Mahadevan]], Lavanya
*"Uttalangadi"   -  [[Manikka Vinayagam]]
*"En Kanave" - [[Srinivas (singer)|Srinivas]], [[Sujatha Mohan|Sujatha]]

==Critical reception==
Hindu wrote:"first half of the film is the screenplay that allows no room for sluggishness or dampeners. The film moves on at breakneck speed and by the time you take a breather it's intermission".<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.hindu.com/fr/2003/10/24/stories/2003102401450200.htm | location=Chennai, India | work=The Hindu | title=Ottran | date=2003-10-24}}</ref>

